n football cups]]\n[[Category:2011\u201312 in Portuguese football]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2015}}\n{{Infobox international football competition\n| tourney_name   = Ta\u00e7a da Liga\n| year           = 2011\u201312\n| other_titles   =\n| image          =\n| size           =\n| caption        =\n| country        = Portugal\n| dates          = 31 July 2011 \u2013 14 April 2012\n| num_teams      = 32\n| confederations =\n| venues         =\n| cities         =\n| champion_other = [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] (4th title)\n| count          = \n| second_other   = [[Gil Vicente F.C.|Gil Vicente]]\n| matches        = 67\n| goals          = 160\n| attendance     = \n| top_scorer     = {{ubl|[[Miguel Rosa]]|[[Baba Diawara]]|[[Rodrigo (footballer, born 1991)|Rodrigo]]}} (4 goals each)\n| player         =\n| prevseason     = [[2010\u201311 Ta\u00e7a da Liga|2010\u201311]]\n| nextseason     = [[2012\u201313 Ta\u00e7a da Liga|2012\u201313]]\n}}\nThe '''2011\u201312 Ta\u00e7a da Liga''' was the fifth edition of the Portuguese [[Ta\u00e7a da Liga]]. The first matches were played on 31 July 2011. The final was played on 14 April 2012, with [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] defeating [[Gil Vicente F.C.|Gil Vicente]] 2\u20131 to win their fourth consecutive Ta\u00e7a da Liga.\n\n==Format==\nThis seasons' format consists of 3 rounds, plus knockout stages. In the first round, only [[Liga de Honra|second division]] teams play. All 16 teams are allocated into 4 groups of 4 teams each. Each team plays 3 matches and top two of each group advances. In the second round, teams that qualified from previous round are joined by the two [[Liga Sagres]] promoted teams and also the 6 worst in the top league in the previous season. There will be two-legged fixtures in which the winners will advance. The third round is where the remaining top 8 teams from previous season first division enter the competition. Again, as in the first round, the 16 teams are divided into 4 groups and each team will play 3 matches. However this time, only group winners advance. Both semi-finals and finals are one-legged fixtures.\n\n==Participating clubs==\n* Clubs starting from the First Round: [[F.C. Arouca|Arouca]], [[Atl\u00e9tico Clube de Portugal|Atl\u00e9tico CP]], [[C.F. Os Belenenses|Belenenses]], [[S.C. Covilh\u00e3|Covilh\u00e3]], [[C.D. Aves|Desportivo das Aves]], [[G.D. Estoril Praia|Estoril]], [[S.C. Freamunde|Freamunde]], [[Leix\u00f5es S.C.|Leix\u00f5es]], [[Moreirense F.C.|Moreirense]], [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Naval 1\u00ba de Maio|Naval]], [[U.D. Oliveirense|Oliveirense]], [[F.C. Penafiel|Penafiel]], [[Portimonense S.C.|Portimonense]], [[C.D. Santa Clara|Santa Clara]], [[C.D. Trofense|Trofense]], [[C.F. Uni\u00e3o|Uni\u00e3o da Madeira]]\n* Clubs starting from the Second Round: [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Acad\u00e9mica de Coimbra - O.A.F.|Acad\u00e9mica]], [[S.C. Beira-Mar|Beira-Mar]], [[C.D. Feirense|Feirense]], [[Gil Vicente F.C.|Gil Vicente]], [[C.S. Mar\u00edtimo|Mar\u00edtimo]], [[S.C. Olhanense|Olhanense]], [[U.D. Leiria|Uni\u00e3o de Leiria]], [[Vitoria F.C.|Vit\u00f3ria de Set\u00fabal]]\n* Clubs starting from the Third Round: [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]], [[S.C. Braga|Braga]], [[C.D. Nacional|Nacional]], [[F.C. Pa\u00e7os de Ferreira|Pa\u00e7os de Ferreira]], [[FC Porto|Porto]], [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]], [[Sporting Clube de Portugal|Sporting CP]], [[Vitoria S.C.|Vit\u00f3ria de Guimar\u00e3es]]\n\n==First round==\n\n===Group A===\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n\n|team1=BEL|name_BEL=[[C.F. Os Belenenses|Belenenses]]\n|team2=PEN|name_PEN=[[F.C. Penafiel|Penafiel]]\n|team3=TRO|name_TRO=[[C.D. Trofense|Trofense]]\n|team4=LEI|name_LEI=[[Leix\u00f5es S.C.|Leix\u00f5es]]\n|win_BEL=2|draw_BEL=1|loss_BEL=0|gf_BEL=8|ga_BEL=4\n|win_PEN=0|draw_PEN=3|loss_PEN=0|gf_PEN=2|ga_PEN=2\n|win_TRO=0|draw_TRO=2|loss_TRO=1|gf_TRO=3|ga_TRO=5\n|win_LEI=0|draw_LEI=2|loss_LEI=1|gf_LEI=5|ga_LEI=7\n\n|col_A=green1|text_A=Advance to [[#Second round|second roun