{"title_page": "Astroneer", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox video game\n|title = Astroneer\n|image = Astroneer Image1.png \n|caption = ''Astroneer'' concept art\n|developer = System Era Softworks\n|publisher = System Era Softworks\n|engine  = [[Unreal Engine 4]]\n|platforms = {{ubl|[[Microsoft Windows]]|[[Xbox One]]|[[PlayStation 4]]}}\n|released = {{ubl|'''Windows''', '''Xbox One'''|February 6, 2019|'''PlayStation 4'''|November 15, 2019}}\n|genre = [[Sandbox game|Sandbox]], [[Adventure game|adventure]]\n|modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]]\n|designer = Jacob Liechty\n|programmer = {{ubl|Brendan Wilson|Zabir Hoque}}\n|artist = {{ubl|Adam Bromell|Paul Pepera}}\n|composer = [[Machinefabriek|Rutger Zuydervelt]]\n}}\n\n'''''Astroneer''''' is a [[Sandbox game|sandbox]] [[adventure game]] developed by System Era Softworks. An [[early access]] version of the game was released on December 16, 2016, and a 1.0 version of the game was released on February 6, 2019. The player is tasked with colonizing planets, creating structures, and mining resources. ''Astroneer'' has no set goal or storyline, though each planet holds challenges for players to complete. The [[PlayStation 4]] version was released on November 15, 2019.\n\n==Gameplay==\n[[File:Astroneer gameplay.png|thumb|left|The astroneer reshapes the environment using the \"terrain tool\"]]\n\n''Astroneer'' is a [[Sandbox game|sandbox]] [[adventure game]] played from a [[Virtual camera system#Third-person view|third-person view]]. Its [[open world]] planets, wherein [[terraforming]] can take place, are subject to [[procedural generation]], with the exception of some planet specific resources. The player controls an [[astronaut]] (called an astroneer) who navigates on foot, or by [[lunar rover|rover]] or [[spacecraft]].\n\n===Crafting===\nCraftable items include rovers, buggies, spaceshuttles, storage silos, atmospheric condensers, research chambers, component smelters, batteries, generators, turbines, and solar panels. For example, [[Ammonium]] can be converted into [[hydrazine]] fuel for an Astroneer's spacecraft, or used in its raw form to create a limited-use thruster. When low on oxygen, the Astroneer recharges by staying near craftable tethers, which can be chained over long distances to prevent suffocation. As of the game's full release, an \"[[oxygenator]]\" is required to provide extended reach of oxygen when tethering.\n \n===Terrain Tool===\nEvery Astroneer has a Terrain Tool, which allows the player to gather resources and reshape the landscape. Resources, such as organic material, quartz, lithium, ammonium, and resin, are neatly packaged by the Terrain Tool into convenient stacks. These stacks can then be snapped into slots on the Astoneer's backpack, storage units, research chambers, etc. Certain resources, such as titanite or clay, can be smelted or combined into more advanced materials. The Astroneer also has the option to research and craft upgrades to the Terrain Tool, which can be plugged and unplugged at will.\n\n===Backpack===\nOther than the Terrain Tool, the Backpack is the Astroneer's main tool. The Backpack functions as the player's inventory and HUD, with two quick-use slots, eight storage slots, a basic 3D printer, a small internal power supply (shown by a column of yellow segments), and a built-in oxygen tank (shown as a horizontal blue bar). The Terrain Tool, which also has three slots that can be used for storage, hangs from the side of the Backpack when not in use. The Backpack also contains the Research Catalogue, which the player uses to unlock new crafting blueprints.\n\n==Development==\n''Astroneer'' was announced in October 2015 by System Era Softworks<ref name=\"Frank-2015\" /> and is developed with the [[Unreal Engine 4]].<ref name=\"Rowe-2016\" /> The art style is composed of [[Texture (visual arts)|texture]]-less environments,<ref name=\"Totilo-2016\" /> conceptualized by artist John Liberto.<ref name=\"Plunkett-2015\" /> Co-founder and lead artist Paul Pepera died on March 27, 2017, 4 months after ''Astroneer'''s early access release.<ref name=\"Plunkett-2017\" /><ref name=\"Wawro-2017\" />\n\n==Release==\nOn December 16, 2016, ''Astroneer'' was given an early access release,<ref name=\"Warr-2016\" /> which was expected to last a year or two, according to the developer.<ref name=\"MacLeod-2016\" /> The post-alpha, full game release date was February 6, 2019 for Windows and Xbox One. Currently, the game can be purchased and downloaded through Steam with an original soundtrack for an added price. On November 15, 2019, ''Astroneer'' was released to the PlayStation 4.\n\n==Reception==\n{{Video game reviews\n| MC = PC: 71/100<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/astroneer |title=ASTRONEER for PC Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref><br />XONE: 73/100<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/astroneer |title=ASTRONEER for Xbox One Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===Awards===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Award !! Category !! Result !! Ref\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"7\" |2019\n|[[Steam Awards 2019|Steam Awards]]\n| Outstanding Visual Style\n| {{nominated}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/steam-awards-2019-winners-announced/1100-6472457/|title=Steam Awards 2019 Winners Announced|website=GameSpot|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[SXSW Gaming Awards]]\n| Gamer's Voice: Video Game\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"Trent-2019\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |[[2019 Webby Awards|Webby Awards]]\n| Adventure Game\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref name=\"Liao-2019\" />\n|-\n| Best Art Direction (People's Voice)\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Game Design (People's Voice)\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best User Experience\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Visual Design (People's Voice)\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"1\" | 2020\n| 18th Annual G.A.N.G. Awards\n| Best Sound Design for an Indie Game\n| {{pending}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"Wilson-2020\" />\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"Rowe-2016\">{{cite web|url=https://www.unrealengine.com/showcase/inspired-space-inside-the-development-of-astroneer|title=Inspired Space: Inside the Development of Astroneer|first=Brian|last=Rowe|date=May 28, 2016|website=[[Unreal Engine]]}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Warr-2016\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2016/12/12/astroneer-early-access-december-16/|title=Astroneer blasts into Early Access, December 16|first=Philippa|last=Warr|date=December 12, 2016|website=[[Rock, Paper, Shotgun]]}}</ref>\n\n<!--<ref name=\"RochefortRobinson-2016\">{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2016/3/26/11306676/astroneer-gameplay|title=Watch us explore space in Astroneer|first1=Simone|last1=de Rochefort|first2=Nick|last2=Robinson|date=March 26, 2016|website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]}}</ref>-->\n\n<ref name=\"Totilo-2016\">{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/how-the-beautiful-space-game-astroneer-works-1773861479|title=How The Beautiful Space Game Astroneer Works|first=Stephen|last=Totilo|date=April 29, 2016|website=[[Kotaku]]}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Plunkett-2015\">{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/the-gorgeous-art-of-astroneer-1735971876|title=The Gorgeous Art Of Astroneer|first=Luke|last=Plunkett|date=October 11, 2015|website=[[Kotaku]]}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Frank-2015\">{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2015/10/7/9471021/find-space-riches-as-you-run-across-the-universe-in-astroneer|title=Find space riches as you run across the universe in Astroneer|first=Allegra|last=Franks|date=October 7, 2015|website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]}}</ref>\n\n<!--<ref name=\"Sykes-2016\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pcgamer.com/astroneer-early-access-begins-next-week/|title=Astroneer early access begins next week|first=Tom|last=Sykes|date=December 10, 2016|website=[[PC Gamer]]}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Matulef-2016\">{{cite web|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2016-12-09-astroneer-looks-like-the-game-you-may-have-wanted-from-no-mans-sky|title=Astroneer looks like the game you may have wanted from No Man's Sky|first=Jeffrey|last=Matulef|date=December 9, 2016|website=[[Eurogamer]]}}</ref>-->\n\n<ref name=\"MacLeod-2016\">{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/space-survival-game-astroneer-will-kill-you-in-all-the-1790201931|title=Space Survival Game Astroneer Will Kill You In All The Best Ways|first=Riley|last=MacLeod|date=December 16, 2016|website=[[Kotaku]]}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Plunkett-2017\">{{cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/the-fantastic-space-art-of-paul-pepera-1793744552|title=The Fantastic Space Art Of Paul Pepera|first=Luke|last=Plunkett|date=March 28, 2017|website=[[Kotaku]]}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Wawro-2017\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/294685/Obituary_Video_game_artist_and_System_Era_cofounder_Paul_Pepera.php|title=Obituary: Video game artist and System Era cofounder Paul Pepera|first=Alex|last=Wawro|date=March 28, 2017|website=[[Gamasutra]]}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Trent-2019\">{{cite web|url=https://gaming.sxsw.com/news/2019/2019-sxsw-gaming-awards-winners-announced/|title=2019 SXSW Gaming Awards Winners Announced|first=Logan|last=Trent|date=March 17, 2019|website=[[South by Southwest]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190321065552/https://gaming.sxsw.com/news/2019/2019-sxsw-gaming-awards-winners-announced/|archivedate=March 21, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Liao-2019\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2019/4/23/18511329/2019-webby-awards-all-the-winners|title=Here are all the winners of the 2019 Webby Awards|first=Shannon|last=Liao|date=April 23, 2019|website=[[The Verge]]}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Wilson-2020\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thehypemagazine.com/2020/02/game-audio-network-guild-announces-18th-annual-g-a-n-g-award-nominees/|title=Game Audio Network Guild Announces 18th Annual G.A.N.G. Award Nominees|first=Kelly|last=Wilson|date=February 13, 2020|website=The Hype Magazine}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://astroneer.space/}}\n* [https://astroneer.gamepedia.com/ Official wiki] on [[Gamepedia]]\n\n[[Category:2019 video games]]\n[[Category:Early access video games]]\n[[Category:Open world video games]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer and single-player video games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 games]]\n[[Category:Video games using procedural generation]]\n[[Category:Science fiction video games]]\n[[Category:Unreal Engine games]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in the United States]]\n[[Category:Video games set in the 25th century]]\n[[Category:Video games set on fictional planets]]\n[[Category:Video games with cel-shaded animation]]\n[[Category:Windows games]]\n[[Category:Xbox One games]]\n[[Category:Xbox Play Anywhere games]]\n[[Category:Xbox One X enhanced games]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox video game\n|title = Astroneer\n|image = Astroneer Image1.png \n|caption = ''Astroneer'' concept art\n|developer = System Era Softworks\n|publisher = System Era Softworks\n|engine  = [[Unreal Engine 4]]\n|platforms = {{ubl|[[Microsoft Windows]]|[[Xbox One]]|[[PlayStation 4]]}}\n|released = {{ubl|'''Windows''', '''Xbox One'''|February 6, 2019|'''PlayStation 4'''|November 15, 2019}}\n|genre = [[Sandbox game|Sandbox]], [[Adventure game|adventure]]\n|modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]]\n|designer = Jacob Liechty\n|programmer = {{ubl|Brendan Wilson|Zabir Hoque}}\n|artist = {{ubl|Adam Bromell|Paul Pepera}}\n|composer = [[Machinefabriek|Rutger Zuydervelt]]\n}}\n\n'''''Astroneer''''' is a [[Sandbox game|sandbox]] [[adventure game]] developed by System Era Softworks. An [[early access]] version of the game was released on December 16, 2016, and a 1.0 version of the game was released on February 6, 2019. The player is tasked with colonizing planets, creating structures, and mining resources. ''Astroneer'' has no set goal or storyline, though each planet holds challenges for players to complete. The [[PlayStation 4]] version was released on November 15, 2019.\n\n==Gameplay==\n[[File:Astroneer gameplay.png|thumb|left|The astroneer reshapes the environment using the \"terrain tool\"]]\n\n''Astroneer'' is a [[Sandbox game|sandbox]] [[adventure game]] played from a [[Virtual camera system#Third-person view|third-person view]]. Its [[open world]] planets, wherein [[terraforming]] can take place, are subject to [[procedural generation]]; with the exception of some planet specific resources. The player controls an [[astronaut]] (called an astroneer) who navigates on foot, or by [[lunar rover|rover]] or [[spacecraft]].\n\n\n===Crafting===\nCraftable items include rovers, buggies, spaceshuttles, storage silos, atmospheric condensers, research chambers, component smelters, batteries, generators, turbines, and solar panels. For example, [[Ammonium]] can be converted into [[hydrazine]] fuel for an Astroneer's spacecraft, or used in its raw form to create a limited-use thruster. When low on oxygen, the Astroneer recharges by staying near craftable tethers, which can be chained over long distances to prevent suffocation. As of the game's full release, an \"[[oxygenator]]\" is required to provide extended reach of oxygen when tethering.\n \n===Terrain Tool===\nEvery Astroneer has a Terrain Tool, which allows the player to gather resources and reshape the landscape. Resources, such as organic material, quartz, lithium, ammonium, and resin, are neatly packaged by the Terrain Tool into convenient stacks. These stacks can then be snapped into slots on the Astoneer's backpack, storage units, research chambers, etc. Certain resources, such as titanite or clay, can be smelted or combined into more advanced materials. The Astroneer also has the option to research and craft upgrades to the Terrain Tool, which can be plugged and unplugged at will.\n\n===Backpack===\nOther than the Terrain Tool, the Backpack is the Astroneer's main tool. The Backpack functions as the player's inventory and HUD, with two quick-use slots, eight storage slots, a basic 3D printer, a small internal power supply (shown by a column of yellow segments), and a built-in oxygen tank (shown as a horizontal blue bar). The Terrain Tool, which also has three slots that can be used for storage, hangs from the side of the Backpack when not in use. The Backpack also contains the Research Catalogue, which the player uses to unlock new crafting blueprints.\n\n==Development==\n''Astroneer'' was announced in October 2015 by System Era Softworks<ref name=\"Frank-2015\" /> and is developed with the [[Unreal Engine 4]].<ref name=\"Rowe-2016\" /> The art style is composed of [[Texture (visual arts)|texture]]-less environments,<ref name=\"Totilo-2016\" /> conceptualized by artist John Liberto.<ref name=\"Plunkett-2015\" /> Co-founder and lead artist Paul Pepera died on March 27, 2017, 4 months after ''Astroneer'''s early access release.<ref name=\"Plunkett-2017\" /><ref name=\"Wawro-2017\" />\n\n==Release==\nOn December 16, 2016, ''Astroneer'' was given an early access release,<ref name=\"Warr-2016\" /> which was expected to last a year or two, according to the developer.<ref name=\"MacLeod-2016\" /> The post-alpha, full game release date was February 6, 2019 for Windows and Xbox One. Currently, the game can be purchased and downloaded through Steam with an original soundtrack for an added price. On November 15, 2019, ''Astroneer'' was released to the PlayStation 4.\n\n==Reception==\n{{Video game reviews\n| MC = PC: 71/100<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/astroneer |title=ASTRONEER for PC Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref><br />XONE: 73/100<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/astroneer |title=ASTRONEER for Xbox One Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===Awards===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Award !! Category !! Result !! Ref\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"7\" |2019\n|[[Steam Awards 2019|Steam Awards]]\n| Outstanding Visual Style\n| {{nominated}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/steam-awards-2019-winners-announced/1100-6472457/|title=Steam Awards 2019 Winners Announced|website=GameSpot|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[SXSW Gaming Awards]]\n| Gamer's Voice: Video Game\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"Trent-2019\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |[[2019 Webby Awards|Webby Awards]]\n| Adventure Game\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref name=\"Liao-2019\" />\n|-\n| Best Art Direction (People's Voice)\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Game Design (People's Voice)\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best User Experience\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Visual Design (People's Voice)\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"1\" | 2020\n| 18th Annual G.A.N.G. Awards\n| Best Sound Design for an Indie Game\n| {{pending}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"Wilson-2020\" />\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"Rowe-2016\">{{cite web|url=https://www.unrealengine.com/showcase/inspired-space-inside-the-development-of-astroneer|title=Inspired Space: Inside the Development of Astroneer|first=Brian|last=Rowe|date=May 28, 2016|website=[[Unreal Engine]]}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Warr-2016\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2016/12/12/astroneer-early-access-december-16/|title=Astroneer blasts into Early Access, December 16|first=Philippa|last=Warr|date=December 12, 2016|website=[[Rock, Paper, Shotgun]]}}</ref>\n\n<!--<ref name=\"RochefortRobinson-2016\">{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2016/3/26/11306676/astroneer-gameplay|title=Watch us explore space in Astroneer|first1=Simone|last1=de Rochefort|first2=Nick|last2=Robinson|date=March 26, 2016|website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]}}</ref>-->\n\n<ref name=\"Totilo-2016\">{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/how-the-beautiful-space-game-astroneer-works-1773861479|title=How The Beautiful Space Game Astroneer Works|first=Stephen|last=Totilo|date=April 29, 2016|website=[[Kotaku]]}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Plunkett-2015\">{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/the-gorgeous-art-of-astroneer-1735971876|title=The Gorgeous Art Of Astroneer|first=Luke|last=Plunkett|date=October 11, 2015|website=[[Kotaku]]}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Frank-2015\">{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2015/10/7/9471021/find-space-riches-as-you-run-across-the-universe-in-astroneer|title=Find space riches as you run across the universe in Astroneer|first=Allegra|last=Franks|date=October 7, 2015|website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]}}</ref>\n\n<!--<ref name=\"Sykes-2016\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pcgamer.com/astroneer-early-access-begins-next-week/|title=Astroneer early access begins next week|first=Tom|last=Sykes|date=December 10, 2016|website=[[PC Gamer]]}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Matulef-2016\">{{cite web|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2016-12-09-astroneer-looks-like-the-game-you-may-have-wanted-from-no-mans-sky|title=Astroneer looks like the game you may have wanted from No Man's Sky|first=Jeffrey|last=Matulef|date=December 9, 2016|website=[[Eurogamer]]}}</ref>-->\n\n<ref name=\"MacLeod-2016\">{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/space-survival-game-astroneer-will-kill-you-in-all-the-1790201931|title=Space Survival Game Astroneer Will Kill You In All The Best Ways|first=Riley|last=MacLeod|date=December 16, 2016|website=[[Kotaku]]}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Plunkett-2017\">{{cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/the-fantastic-space-art-of-paul-pepera-1793744552|title=The Fantastic Space Art Of Paul Pep