{"title_page": "2010\u201311 Ta\u00e7a da Liga", "text_new": "{{Infobox international football competition\n| tourney_name   = Ta\u00e7a da Liga\n| year           = 2010\u201311\n| other_titles   =\n| image          =\n| size           =\n| caption        =\n| country        = Portugal\n| dates          = 8 August 2010 \u2013 23 April 2011\n| num_teams      = 32\n| confederations =\n| venues         =\n| cities         =\n| champion_other = [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]\n| count          = 3\n| second_other   = [[F.C. Pa\u00e7os de Ferreira|Pa\u00e7os de Ferreira]]\n| matches        = 67\n| goals          = 190\n| attendance     =\n| top_scorer     = [[Hugo Filipe Vieira|Hugo Vieira]] (5 goals)\n| player         =\n| prevseason     = [[2009\u201310 Ta\u00e7a da Liga|2009\u201310]]\n| nextseason     = [[2011\u201312 Ta\u00e7a da Liga|2011\u201312]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2010\u201311 Ta\u00e7a da Liga''' was the fourth edition of the Portuguese [[Ta\u00e7a da Liga]]. The first matches were played on 8 August 2010. The final was played on 23 April 2011 at the [[Est\u00e1dio Cidade de Coimbra]], where [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] beat [[F.C. Pa\u00e7os de Ferreira|Pa\u00e7os de Ferreira]] 2\u20131 to win their third title.\n\n==Format==\nThis seasons' format consists of 3 rounds, plus knockout stages. In the first round only [[Liga de Honra|second division]] teams play. All 16 teams are allocated into four groups of four teams each. Each team plays 3 matches and top two of each group advances. In the second round, teams that qualified from previous round are joined by the two [[Primeira Liga]] promoted teams and also the six-worst in the top league in the previous season. There will be two-legged fixtures in which the winners will advance. The third round is where the remaining top eight teams from previous season first division enter the competition. Again, as in the first round, the 16 teams are divided into four groups and each team will play three matches. However this time, only group winners advance. Both semi-finals and finals are one-legged fixtures.\n\n==Participating clubs==\n* Clubs starting from the First Round: [[Gil Vicente F.C.|Gil Vicente]], [[G.D. Estoril Praia|Estoril]], [[C.D. Aves|Desportivo das Aves]], [[Varzim S.C.|Varzim]], [[C.D. Santa Clara|Santa Clara]], [[S.C. Freamunde|Freamunde]], [[C.D. Feirense|Feirense]], [[U.D. Oliveirense|Oliveirense]], [[S.C. Covilh\u00e3|Covilh\u00e3]], [[C.D. Trofense|Trofense]], [[C.D. F\u00e1tima|F\u00e1tima]], [[F.C. Penafiel|Penafiel]], [[F.C. Arouca|Arouca]], [[Moreirense F.C.|Moreirense]], [[C.F. Os Belenenses|Belenenses]], [[Leix\u00f5es S.C.|Leix\u00f5es]]\n* Clubs starting from the Second Round: [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Acad\u00e9mica de Coimbra - O.A.F.|Acad\u00e9mica]], [[F.C. Pa\u00e7os de Ferreira|Pa\u00e7os de Ferreira]], [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]], [[U.D. Leiria|Uni\u00e3o de Leiria]], [[S.C. Olhanense|Olhanense]], [[Vitoria F.C.|Vit\u00f3ria de Set\u00fabal]], [[S.C. Beira-Mar|Beira-Mar]], [[Portimonense S.C.|Portimonense]]\n* Clubs starting from the Third Round: [[FC Porto|Porto]], [[Sporting Clube de Portugal|Sporting CP]], [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]], [[C.D. Nacional|Nacional]], [[S.C. Braga|Braga]], [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Naval 1\u00ba de Maio|Naval]], [[Vitoria S.C.|Vit\u00f3ria de Guimar\u00e3es]], [[C.S. Mar\u00edtimo|Mar\u00edtimo]]\n\n==First round==\n\n===Group A===\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n|section=R1GA\n\n|team1=FAT|name_FAT=[[C.D. F\u00e1tima|F\u00e1tima]]\n|team2=GIV|name_GIV=[[Gil Vicente F.C.|Gil Vicente]]\n|team3=MOR|name_MOR=[[Moreirense F.C.|Moreirense]]\n|team4=FEI|name_FEI=[[C.D. Feirense|Feirense]]\n|win_FAT=1|draw_FAT=2|loss_FAT=0|gf_FAT=5|ga_FAT=4\n|win_GIV=1|draw_GIV=1|loss_GIV=1|gf_GIV=5|ga_GIV=5\n|win_MOR=0|draw_MOR=3|loss_MOR=0|gf_MOR=4|ga_MOR=4\n|win_FEI=0|draw_FEI=2|loss_FEI=1|gf_FEI=4|ga_FEI=5\n\n|col_A=green1|text_A=Advance to [[#Second round|second round]]\n|result1=A|result2=A\n\n|show_matches=y\n|short_st